Program to take a number from user and print true if the number is a three digit number and also ends with 7 otherwise print False.

# Take input for the number
number = int(input("Enter a number: "))

# Check if the number is a three-digit number and ends with 7
is_valid = (100 <= number <= 999) and (number % 10 == 7)

# Print the result
print("Is the number a three-digit number that ends with 7:", is_valid)
